subSubSection.paragraph:
The representatives of the genus 

Liroetoides

have closed anterior coxal cavities (open in 

Liroetis

), posterior margin of abdominal ventrite V in male with three more or less developed subtriangular processes (cf. drawings in Bൾඓൽෂĸ (2013), processes missing in 

Liroetis

), and aedeagus long and narrow, without elevated lateral subtriangular plates (present in 

Liroetis

).
